The paper discusses text analysis techniques such as top-k keyword and document extraction, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) applications. The paper also focuses on benchmarking different weighting schemes and database implementations, which are important topics in database systems (DB) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.DB, followed by cs.CL (NLP), cs.DS (data structures), and cs.AI (machine learning).
